  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the transfer function (electro-optical/opto-electronic) of a color space using CICP identifiers.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp` corresponds to the `transfer_characteristics` field defined in
ISO/IEC 23091-2 and ITU-T H.273. Each member maps to a numeric code point that identifies a
transfer function relating scene luminance to encoded signal values.

Use these values with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp*> to create a color space
from standard CICP descriptors.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create a Rec. 2020 color space with HLG transfer function
var colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec2020,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Hlg);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
